items.title: Why the Market Dipped But Goldman Sachs (GS) Gained Today
items.description: Goldman Sachs (GS) concluded the recent trading session at $635.24, signifying a +1.7% move from its prior day's close.

items.title: US Plans to Ease Capital Rule Limiting Banks Treasury Trades
items.description: (Bloomberg) -- The top US bank regulators plan to reduce a key capital buffer by up to 1.5 percentage points for the biggest lenders after concerns that it constrained their trading in the $29 trillion Treasuries market.
